Depending on production levels, pheasants are released once prior to the pheasant hunting season and then twice a week for the first two to three weeks of the season. After that, birds are released about once a week until the 9-day gun deer season. Hunting Season (Pheasant) and Requirements ¶ October 14, 2023 (9 AM) through January 7, 2024 Bag Limit is one rooster per day for opening day (October 14-15) and two roosters per day for the remainder of the season. Pheasant Hunters need a valid small game hunting license and a 2023 Pheasant Stamp Fields & Forest Lands Interactive Gamebird Hunting Tool (FFLIGHT) ¶ Online map showing properties stocked with pheasants, managed dove fields and suitable cover for ruffed grouse and woodcock. Visit https://dnr.wi.gov and search keyword FFLIGHT for more information. 12PM Closure Areas ¶ Properties where pheasant hunting hours close at 12pm on weekdays beginning the third day of the season and continuing through November 3rd. The remainder of the season and all other properties follow regular small game hunting hours listed in the combined hunting regulations. All other properties only allow the harvest of roosters.
